results.name: a(n) is the largest number such that all of a(n)'s length-n substrings are distinct and divisible by 89.
example: a(4) is 338277 because its length-4 substrings (3382, 3827, 8277) are all distinct and divisible by 89 and there is no larger number with this property.
results.author: _Hans Havermann_, Mar 29 2004
